==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sippet
<hw>Sip"pet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Sip</er>,
<er>Sop</er>.]</ety> <def>A small sop; a small, thin piece of toasted
bread soaked in milk, broth, or the like; a small piece of toasted or
fried bread cut into some special shape and used for
garnishing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your sweet <qex>sippets</qex> in widows' houses.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sipple</ent>⟦br⟧
